It was a night of bliss as the world’s awarded deluxe whisky Johnnie Walker Black Label and Cubana Lounge, hosted Lagos’ top socialites and ‘walkerholics’ at Nigeria’s biggest afro-jazz platform Johnnie, Jazz and Whisky.
.
With a wide range of cocktails and finger foods, guests enjoyed awesome performances including spoken word renditions capped off by a special set put together by Temmie Ovwasa of YBNL. Adekunle Gold took the stage later in the evening and brought the audience to its feet with his smash hits. From ‘Orente’ to ‘Ire’, the master crooner had the crowd under his sway delivering a memorable performance. In every aspect of the night, flavour was king and afro-jazz was the beat. click to see images of the event: